Create the thin Hono route handler for `GET /api/v1/protected/recommendations`. Route stays thin — all business logic lives in RecommendationService.

Files affected (all new):
- `apps/api/src/routes/recommendations/protected/get.ts` — route handler
- `apps/api/src/routes/recommendations/protected/index.ts` — barrel: `export const protectedRecommendationRoutes = ...`
- `apps/api/src/routes/recommendations/index.ts` — top-level barrel: `export { protectedRecommendationRoutes } from './protected'`

Route implementation pattern (follow `search-history/protected/list.ts`):
```ts
export const getRecommendationsRoute = createProtectedRoute({
  method: 'get',
  path: '/',
  summary: 'Get personalized recommendations',
  tags: ['Recommendations'],
  responseSchema: RecommendationFeedSchema,
  options: {
    middlewares: [entitlementMiddleware(), gateRecommendations()],
  },
  handler: async (ctx) => {
    const actor = getActorFromContext(ctx);
    const query = RecommendationQuerySchema.parse(ctx.req.query());
    const service = new RecommendationService({ logger: apiLogger });
    const result = await service.getRecommendations(actor, { limit: query.limit });
    if (result.error) throw new ServiceError(result.error.code, result.error.message);
    return result.data;
  }
});
```

Note: `entitlementMiddleware()` must run before `gateRecommendations()` (loads entitlements into context first). Verify this ordering matches how gateSearchHistory is wired in the search-history route.

Acceptance criteria:
- Route registered correctly at GET /
- Entitlement middleware runs before gate
- Query param `limit` is validated via Zod before use
- Returns 403 for actors lacking CAN_VIEW_RECOMMENDATIONS
- Returns 200 with RecommendationFeed body for entitled actors

Testing requirements:
- Integration test written in T-015
- For this task: verify `pnpm typecheck` passes in apps/api

Create the Astro SSR page that hosts the recommendations feed island. Follows the pattern of `mi-cuenta/historial-busquedas/index.astro`.

Files affected:
- `apps/web/src/pages/[lang]/mi-cuenta/recomendaciones/index.astro` — new file

Page implementation pattern (follow historial-busquedas/index.astro exactly):
```astro
---
const locale = Astro.locals.locale as SupportedLocale;
const user = Astro.locals.user;
if (!user) return Astro.redirect(buildUrl({ locale, path: 'auth/signin' }));

const { t } = createTranslations(locale);
const title = t('account.pages.recommendations.title', 'Para vos');
const description = t('account.pages.recommendations.description', '...');
const apiUrl = getApiUrl();

// Server-side prefetch (non-blocking)
let initialData = null;
try {
  const cookieHeader = Astro.request.headers.get('cookie');
  if (cookieHeader) {
    const res = await fetch(`${apiUrl}/api/v1/protected/recommendations`, {
      headers: { cookie: cookieHeader }
    });
    if (res.ok) initialData = await res.json();
  }
} catch { /* silently degrade */ }
---
<AccountLayout locale={locale} title={title} description={description} activeSection="recomendaciones">
  <RecommendationsFeed client:visible {apiUrl} {locale} {initialData} />
</AccountLayout>
```

Details:
- `prerender = false` (SSR required — auth context)
- Auth guard: redirect to signin if no user
- Server-side prefetch is non-blocking: catch block renders island without initial data
- Uses `AccountLayout` (same as all other mi-cuenta pages)
- `client:visible` directive (island loads when scrolled into view)

Acceptance criteria:
- Unauthenticated users are redirected to signin
- Authenticated users see the recommendations feed
- Page title and description use i18n keys
- Server-side prefetch silently degrades on error

Testing requirements:
- Astro-level testing is minimal — the island (T-011) has the comprehensive test suite
- Manual verification: page renders with SSR, redirects unauthenticated users
- Integration test in T-015 covers the API layer; T-016 covers the island
